e discipline of creation, be it to paint, compose, write, is an effort towards wholeness.\n\n- Madeleine L'Engle, Walking on Water: Reflections on Faith and Art\n|\nWhen the wind blows,the grass bends.\n\n- Confucius, The Analects\n|\nLife's managed, not cured.\n\n- Phillip\n|\nAnd now we step to the rhythm of miracles.--from The Light, That Never Dies\n\n- Aberjhani, Elemental: The Power of Illuminated Love\n|\nBelief isn't simply a thing for fair times and bright days, I think. What is belief- what is faith- if you don't continue in it after failure.\n\n- Brandon Sanderson, The Final Empire\n|\nIf you really want to learn, do not be surprised if someone tries to teach you. And do not lightly reject the method.\n\n- Idries Shah, Learning How to Learn: Psychology and Spirituality in the Sufi Way\n|\nKashays [anger-pride-deceit-greed] will not leave by suppressing them, they go away through Gnan (Enlightened Knowledge).\n\n- Dada\n|\nI intend all my characters must escape from impossible situations; if they are not in trouble, then as a writer, I am.\n\n- Cleveland\n|\nEvery man should believe in something.If not..he would doubt everything, even himself.\n\n- Toba Beta, Master of Stupidity\n|\nAll was in God's plan, and he had to accept even as he didn't understand.\n\n- Barbara Cameron, A Time to Love\n|\nFalling in love with humans is like walking into a pantry and realizing you're trapped in it without Whip Cream, and Cherries.\n\n- AainaA-Ridtz\n|\nFor if we're destroyed, the knowledge is dead...We're nothing more than dust jackets for books...so many pages to a person...\n\n- Ray Bradbury, Fahrenheit 451\n|\nIt is uncertainty which fills life with beauty, excitement, and joy.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIt is not about the building, but about what the building can produce.\n\n- ANIKOR\n|\nCheating is pure hypocrisy. Our partner deserves better than that. If we don’t love someone, we should not be with them. That would also be hypocrisy.\n\n- Cathy Burnham Martin, The Bimbo Has Brains: And Other Freaky Facts\n|\nIt is books that are a key to the wide world; if you can't do anything else, read all that you can.\n\n- Jane\n|\nWhen we're determined to reach an objective, it's the gap between where we are and where we aspire to be that lights a fire under us.\n\n- Adam M. Grant, Originals: How Non-Conformists Move the World\n|\nI have done what people do, my life makes a reasonable showing. Can I go back to my books now?\n\n- Lynne Sharon Schwartz, Ruined By Reading: A Life in Books\n|\nRemember, purpose is about giving...All you can do with your life is to give it away in the service of others.\n\n- Wayne\n|\nWe all fail at certain points in our lives, but if your journey stops at failure, it will become your destination.\n\n- Hassnain\n|\nWe are a part of love, not separate from it\n\n- Richard\n|\nI didnt pay atteniton to times or distance, instead focusing on how it felt just to be in motion, knowing it wasn't about the finish line but how I got there that mattered.\n\n- Sarah Dessen, The Truth About Forever\n|\nWhen I saw you, I discovered love!\n\n- Avijeet\n|\nReligious belief is without reason and without dignity, and its record is near-universally dreadful.\n\n- Martin Amis, The Second Plane: 14 Responses to September 11\n|\nA positive attitude causes a chain reaction of positive thoughts, events, and outcomes.\n\n- Wade\n|\nOn even the darkest of days, the brightest thing in my life is you.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nI stay cool, and dig all jive,That's the way I stay alive.My motto, as I live and learn, isDig and be dugIn return.\n\n- Langston\n|\nWhat are you?” he demanded. “A slayer?' I rolled my eyes. “The name's Val, not Buffy. Do I look like a blond cheerleader with questionable taste in men?\n\n- Parker Blue, Bite Me\n|\nYou have a very open relationship with your fans.''Yes. We have an open relationship. Obviously they can see other authors if they want, and I can see other readers.\n\n- Neil\n|\nThe naively cynical measure a piece of legislation, a victory, a milestone not against the past or the limits of the possible, but against their ideas of perfection...\n\n- Rebecca Solnit, Hope in the Dark\n|\nNothing is build, just like that, everything around the world has some value and the purpose.\n\n- Santosh Kalwar, Nature God\n|\nDon't just become a monument of information, rather a solace of knowledge refuge.\n\n- Unarine\n|\nWe don’t even ask happiness, just a little less pain.\n\n- Charles\n|\nNo tricks, no tools, but talent makes a task truly top class.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nI always thought time was the most valuable currency, but I realized the people we spent our time on and loved us back, that love held even more meaning to me.\n\n- Hubert\n|\nA library bears similar qualities to a hospital. Librarians are like doctors, books the prescriptions.\n\n- Trudy Wallis, Longbourn Library: A Novel of Pride, Prejudice, and Books\n|\nTo hope for nothing, to expect nothing, to demand nothing. This is analytical despair.\n\n- James Hillman, Suicide and the Soul\n|\nGods have become like us, ergo, we have become like gods. And to you, my unknown planetary readers, we will come to you, to make your life as divinely rational and exact as ours.\n\n- Yavgeny\n|\nEducation is important not because it helps you to get a job, but because it opens the window of the mind through which we can see the beauty of life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThe fact that we can never have complete, perfect knowledge does not absolve us of the moral duty to judge and to take a stand against evil.\n\n- Ken Liu, The Man Who Ended History: A Documentary\n|\nThere was a time when people accepted magical experiences as natural. There were no priests then, and no one went chasing after the secrets of the occult.\n\n- Paulo\n|\nGod turns you from one feeling to another and teaches by means of opposites so that you will have two wings to fly, not one\n\n- Jalaluddin Rumi, The Essential Rumi"